laboratory_examinations.findings: Serum alkaline phosphatase: 670 IU/L (normal value: 40–160 IU/L) - markedly increased; Osteocalcin: 219.6 ng/ml (normal value: 11–43 ng/ml) - markedly increased; Serum calcium concentration: within the reference range; other endocrine indices not abnormal.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: Alkaline phosphatase levels decreased to 538 IU/L in July 2010, then decreased further to 403 IU/L in December 2013. Osteocalcin levels decreased to 192.5 ng/ml in July 2010, then increased to 246.30 ng/ml in December 2013.
